The women battled to improve safety at sea for trawlermen at a time when many were drowning or being injured. In one week in 1968 three fishing vessels were lost in violent seas. As families mourned, a meeting was called asking for safety improvements. "It became my life and my job," she said at the time. Their efforts led to 88 safety improvements. Born Yvonne Marie Horsfield, she was the eldest of six children. She is survived by her four children. Her husband, John Blenkinsop, died in 2004.